narratives.question_text: How clearly did the instructor define the topic of study?
comments: Syllabus was extremely clear and covered the topics that I believe were relevant to the application of hydraulics that I may have in the future.

narratives.question_text: How clearly did the instructor outline the expectation for the course, classroom activity and homework?
How well were individual class sessions prepared and presented?
comments: I really enjoyed the hands on days. Getting to touch and see the real thing rather then just a picture help further my understanding

Power points, handouts, and project lists were very clear. The notes and comments are particularly helpful in pointing out the topic of discussion and a good reference to look back on in the future. The course material was very well prepared throughout the entire course.

narratives.question_text: How well did lectures fit within the boundaries of the course?

comments: There could be more small projects or little assignments.
There could have been more homework. The hydraulics hands on was GREAT. I know its hard to find time but more hands on would have been great.

narratives.question_text: How available was the instructor for help outside the classroom?
comments: Always available and happy to help

narratives.question_text: How useful were assignments in furthering an understanding of the topic?
comments: Actually being able to to do the thing we talk about in class is my favorite and the way that i learn best. The Hydraulics project this year, although messy and frustrating was enormously helpful in understanding how a system works and what REALLY takes to create one

The practical hydraulics project was incredibly helpful in learning about hydraulic systems. That was the highlight of the course. As discussed in class following the completion of the project, It would have been nice if the components were already laid out in front of us. While it valuable to dig through trays of hydraulic fittings, I feel as if the specification of components on paper would be more than sufficient for our understand of fittings. The physical assembly of the components could be more straight forward and laid out in front of us.

narratives.question_text: If tests were given, how fairly did they measure knowledge gained?
comments: I don't think we had test this semester. Physics and automation and hydraulics and pneumatic are all starting to blend together for me.

narratives.question_text: How useful was this course in preparing you for production work?
comments: Although I have not yet been called on to use this knowledge, I now have a place to start, a basic understanding and lots of resources to turn to

It was incredibly useful for production work. Much of the course material was familiar to me because I designed a hydraulic system for production work. Having taken the class, it has added to my understanding of hydraulic systems and the variety of hydraulic systems that exist beyond that of YRT.

narratives.question_text: How would you evaluate the instructor's knowledge of the material?
Please offer additional comments on such topics as: what worked best about the course, suggested improvements, class materials, etc.
comments: I would love to do more small lab days like we did in automation. Just a chance to put more of what we learn into practice.
